    "result": {"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"title":"Task 43","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>When you talk about objects or things in a specific place, you often use the word <code>that</code> to point them out. For example, <code>that shelf</code> means the shelf you are talking about or focusing on at the moment.</p>\n<p>The word <code>shelf</code> is a noun that refers to a flat, horizontal surface used for holding items. When you talk about more than one <code>shelf</code>, you should change the ending to make it plural by replacing <code>f</code> with <code>ves</code>, so it becomes <code>shelves</code>. For example, <code>one shelf</code>, <code>two shelves</code>.</p>\n</section>","instructions":null,"challengeType":22,"helpCategory":"English","superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","block":"learn-how-to-talk-about-hobbies-and-interests","fields":{"blockName":"learn-how-to-talk-about-hobbies-and-interests","slug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-talk-about-hobbies-and-interests/task-43","tests":[]},"fillInTheBlank":{"sentence":"<p>Hey, I noticed you have a huge collection of action figures on _ _ behind you. Are you a collector?</p>","blanks":[{"answer":"that","feedback":"<p>This word is used to specify which shelf James is talking about.</p>"},{"answer":"shelf","feedback":"<p>It's a flat and horizontal surface. You should use its singular form.</p>"}]},"scene":{"setup":{"background":"company2-center.png","characters":[{"character":"James","position":{"x":50,"y":15,"z":1.2},"opacity":0}],"audio":{"filename":"3.2-3.mp3","startTime":1,"startTimestamp":0,"finishTimestamp":5.18},"alwaysShowDialogue":null},"commands":[{"background":null,"character":"James","position":null,"opacity":1,"startTime":0,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null},{"background":null,"character":"James","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":1,"finishTime":6.18,"dialogue":{"text":"Hey, I noticed you have a huge collection of action figures on that shelf